    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2011 Porsche Cayman S (987.2), a quintessential mid-engine platform featuring the highly desirable 3.4L Direct Fuel Injection (DFI) flat-six. This powerplant is mated to a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle, offering a mechanical connection lost in modern EPS systems. The vehicle's kinematics are sharp, aided by a low polar moment of inertia and a well-sorted MacPherson strut suspension. Performance is bolstered by a factory-optioned limited-slip differential and an active rear aero element. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain is internally sound with no signs of bore scoring or IMS concerns common in earlier iterations. It has been meticulously maintained with regular oil analysis and recent bushing refreshes to ensure optimal chassis rigidity and steering precision.",
